Police in Embu West subcounty early Friday shot dead two suspected robbers as they attempted to break into a shop. County Commissioner Edison Nyale said the officers were tipped off by members of the public. "The police fired about five shots, although they got away, we have managed to get the two who succumbed to gunshot wounds in their car," Nyale said. Two were found dead in their get away car but their accomplices are still on the run and are being pursued by police. The police boss said the suspects disobeyed orders to surrender and shot back at the officers. Nyale said the slain suspects are well known and have been identified by the community members. He said the suspects are notorious robbers, as per the locals' account. Area residents thanked the officers for their swift response to the suspects' latest criminal acts. The police called on the suspects who got away to surrender themselves and the weapons they were using to authorities.